1.0    Executive Summary

Air Liquide Large Industries US, L.P. (Air Liquide) operates a hydrogen plant within the Chevron refinery located in El Segundo, California (Chevron El Segundo Refinery).  This document addresses the requirements of the United States Environmental Protection Agency's (EPA) Risk Management Program (RMP) and the California Accidental Release Program (CalARP) with regards to the pentane processes on site.  The following summarizes the required elements of a Program 1 facility. 

1.1    ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES

 "Our commitment to Safety and Environmental Protection in the Air Liquide, El Segundo Hydrogen Plant must extend beyond the gates. As part of the community, we have a responsibility to our customers and to those who live in the surrounding area to help provide a safe working and living environment. Through safety, concern for the environment, and community involvement, we can develop a true partnership with our customers and neighbors."

The Hydrogen Facility has accidental release protection programs for all covered processes, which includes a prevention program with the following elements:

A?    Maintaining up-to-date safety information;
A?    Conducting a process hazard analysis;
A?    Implementing operating procedures;
A?    Implementing a staff training program;
A?    Implementing a maintenance program;
A?    Conducting compliance audits; and
A?    Conducting incident investigations.

An Emergency Action Plan has been developed to help instruct personnel how to respond in case of an emergency.  Emergency response actions involve the system operators and maintenance staff, as well as the local El Segundo Fire Department. In addition, the Plant Manager or an appointed representative serves as the focal point during and following an accidental release for notifying the Chevron El Segundo Refinery, reporting to the appropriate agencies, and providing information to the public.

