1.4    GENERAL ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM

In addition to the CalARP and EPA RMP regulations, processes at the Hydrogen Facility are also subject to the OSHA Process Safety Management (PSM) standard.   Although not required for Program 1 facilities under CalARP and EPA RMP regulations, a prevention program has been developed by the Hydrogen Facility that includes the following elements (also indicates the applicable internal regulation number): 

A?    Employee participation in process safety management and accident prevention (El Segundo SMR Employee Participation for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes, ELS-SMR-0101-P);
A?    Process safety information to address chemical properties and associated hazards, equipment design/configuration information, specific chemical inventories and operation limits for key process parameters (El Segundo SMR Process Safety Information for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes, ELS-SMR-0102-P); 
A?    Process hazard analysis to help ensure that hazards associated with the various processes are identified and controlled (El Segundo SMR Process Hazard Analysis for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes, ELS-SMR-0103-P);
A?    Maintenance of written operating procedures that address various modes of process operations;  
A?    Implementation of a formal training program for all employees involved in operating the process (El Segundo SMR Training Program for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes, ELS-SMR-0104-P
A?    Pre-startup safety reviews of new/modified facilities or processes before placing those facilities or processes

into service (El Segundo SMR Pre-Startup Safety Review for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes, ELS-SMR-0106-P);
A?    Practices and procedures to ensure mechanical integrity and to maintain pressure vessels, piping systems, relief valve and vent systems, controls, pumps, compressors, and emergency shutdown systems in a safe operating condition (Mechanical Integrity: El Segundo, CA SMR CalARP/RMP/PSM Document, PPN-MNT-1004-P);
A?    Safe work practices in place to help ensure employee and process safety (Safe Work, ALA-HSE-2000-P, El Segundo SMR Hot Work for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes, ELS-SMR-0107-P, El Segundo SMR Energy Control and Isolation for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes, ELS-SMR-0112-P, and El Segundo SMR Confined Space Entry for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes, ELS-SMR-0113-P);
A?    Management of change requirements for ensuring that proposed process or equipment changes or changes indirectly affecting processes are evaluated, approved and documented prior to implementation (Management of Change ALAC-EXE-0003-P and El Segundo SMR Management of Change for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes ELS-SMR-0108-P); 
A?    Incident investigation and reporting to proactively identify root causes and correct them rather than simply addressing the symptom of the incident (Large Industries Communication and Reporting of Incidents OPS-QUA-002-P and El Segundo SMR Incident Investigation for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes ELS-SMR-0109-P); and 
A?    Compliance audits to help ensure the accident prevention program is functioning properly (El Segundo SMR Compliance Audits for PSM/RMP/CalARP Covered Processes ELS-SMR-0111-P). 

